TY  - JOUR
AU  - Khorana, Ajay
AU  - Servaes, Henri
T1  - The Determinants of Mutual Fund Starts
PY  - 1999
Y1  - 1999/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/12.5.1043
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 12
IS  - 5
SP  - 1043
EP  - 1074
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - For a sample of 1163 mutual funds started over the period 1979–1992, we find that fund initiations are positively related to the level of assets invested in and the capital gains embedded in other funds with the same objective, the fund family's prior performance, the fraction of funds in the family in the low range of fees, and the decision by large families to open similar funds in the prior year. In addition, consistent with the presence of scale and scope economies in fund openings, we find that large families and families that have more experience in opening funds in the past are more likely to open new funds.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/12.5.1043
ER  - 



